26/12/2010
BELGRADE, Serbia -- War Crimes Prosecutor Vladimir Vukcevic announced on Friday (December 24th) that German police have arrested a former member of the "The Jackals" paramilitary unit, wanted for1999 war crimes in Kosovo. 
Zoran Obradovic is one of the main suspects in connection with crimes committed in the village of Cuska. 
The trial of nine other former members of "The Jackals" for the brutal killing of over 40 ethnic Albanian civilians during the 1999 war in Kosovo began on December 20th in Belgrade. 
Seventeen other suspects remain at large. 
(Tanjug, Beta, B92, AFP, AP - 24/12/10)
